      "writtenOn": "2025-11-21T20:14:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So, the getJsonObj() call was causing errors with the unit tests since it tries to search a path for a json config to use to set the trust manager. Since trust groups are an older workaround that don\u0027t need to be supported anymore, I removed that call and had it create and store an empty trust manager instead (since you still need one to pass to the Fan constructor). As for whether there is a difference between yaml and json operation, Matt had said that the new fan monitor code doesn\u0027t need to support yaml, so I haven\u0027t made much differentiation. \n\nWith that being said, might be able to remove the setTrustMgr() and/or getTrustGroups() functions from this file, since we\u0027re not doing much with the trust groups. I\u0027ll ask Matt about it after next week.",
